latestPosts.caption:
2024 was filled with changes i never knew i’d have to go through. i lost a lot but i won some too. i moved back home after 3 years, started building my business, travelled around and worked on myself - and all of this was possible because of the people i was surrounded with, i couldn’t be more grateful. 

and now i know the only way is up 💗

happy 2025 ✨

merry christmas from my bundle of joy to yours 🤍🎄

i started this christmas portrait tradition back in 2018 (you might see my glow up as well as the tree’s 🤭), i literally wake up on christmas day looking forward to click these. this year though, was bittersweet - not having my angel doggos next to me hit me so hard. but i know they’re looking over us and indulging in all the zoomies and cuddles like they used to together ✨

so here’s to love and being grateful for all the things that life has offered us, MERRRY CHRISTMAS! 🥰
